 gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="111">This means <strong data-start="11" data-end="78">PostgreSQL is installed, but <code data-start="42" data-end="48">psql</code> is not in your Windows PATH</strong>. We can still fix your database.</p>
<h2 data-start="113" data-end="147">Option 1: Use pgAdmin (easiest)</h2>
<ol data-start="149" data-end="377">
<li data-start="149" data-end="171">
<p data-start="152" data-end="171">Open <strong data-start="157" data-end="170">pgAdmin 4</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="172" data-end="209">
<p data-start="175" data-end="209">Connect to your PostgreSQL server.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="210" data-end="336">
<p data-start="213" data-end="220">Expand:</p>
